    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2422: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Department’s 181, April 8, 10 p.m. The Prime Minister<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d297fn19">Carlos Saladrigas.</note> enthusiastically endorses the
                    establishment of patrols based on San <pb facs="0274" n="260" xml:id="pg_260"/>
                    Julián “or at any other point in Cuba from which we desire to operate”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
